📋 Remaining 3 Hooks to Integrate
Based on our current progress (3/6 hooks integrated at 50%), here are the remaining 3 hooks that need to be integrated:

🔍 Remaining Hooks Overview
🎯 Current Status:

✅ useUserData - Integrated (user interactions: favorites, shortlist, exclusions)
✅ useSearchPagination - Integrated (pagination and infinite scroll)
✅ useSearchViewModes - Integrated (view mode management)
🔄 Remaining 3 Hooks
1. useSearchFilters (259 lines)
🎯 Purpose: Manage search filters and saved searches

Filter options - All search criteria state
Saved searches - Load, save, delete, schedule searches
Filter functions - Apply, clear, reset filters
Risk: LOW (isolated functionality)
📦 What it will replace:

savedSearches, showSavedSearches, showSaveModal state
loadSavedSearches, handleSaveSearch, handleDeleteSavedSearch functions
Filter option loading functions
Filter state management
2. useSearchState (274 lines)
🎯 Purpose: Core search state management

Search results - users, loading, error state
Search criteria - Complete search parameters
Pagination state - currentPage, totalResults, hasMoreResults
Search execution - handleSearch function
Risk: HIGH (core functionality)
📦 What it will replace:

users, loading, error, initialSearchComplete state
searchCriteria, currentPage, totalResults, hasMoreResults state
handleSearch function and related search logic
Session management and state persistence
3. useSearchActions (471 lines)
🎯 Purpose: API calls and user actions

Profile actions - handleProfileAction, handleMessage, handlePIIRequest
Search actions - handleLoadSavedSearch, handleClearFilters
PII management - loadPiiRequests, hasPiiAccess, isPiiRequestPending
Risk: MEDIUM (complex interactions)
📦 What it will replace:

handleProfileAction, handleMessage, handlePIIRequestSuccess functions
loadPiiRequests, hasPiiAccess, isPiiRequestPending functions
handleLoadSavedSearch, handleDeleteSavedSearch, handleSaveSearch functions
PII access management and user interaction handlers
📊 Integration Priority
🎯 Recommended Order:

useSearchState (HIGH priority) - Core foundation
useSearchFilters (LOW risk) - Isolated functionality
useSearchActions (MEDIUM risk) - Final integration
🔧 Why This Order:

useSearchState provides the foundation for the other two
useSearchFilters is low-risk and isolated
useSearchActions ties everything together
🚀 Expected Final Result
After integrating all 6 hooks:

Modular architecture with complete separation of concerns
Significantly reduced SearchPage2.js component size
Reusable hooks that can be used in other components
Testable units for better code quality
Maintainable codebase for future development
